 Katori, T. and Kralik, R. and Latham, N. and Ramsden, R. M. and Ito, H. and Sone, T. and Suzuki, A. T. and Takeuchi, Y. and Wada, S. and Zhong, H. and Feng, J. and Feng, L. and Han, S. and Hikida, J. and Hu, J. R. and Hu, Z. and Kawaue, M. and Kikawa, T. and Ngoc, T. V. and Nakaya, T. and Wendell, R. A. and Jenkins, S. J. and McCauley, N. and Tarrant, A. and Fan`ı, M. and Wilking, M. J. and Xie, Z. and Fukuda, Y. and Menjo, H. and Yoshioka, Y. and Lagoda, J. and Mandal, M. and Zalipska, J. and Mori, M. and Jiang, J. and Hamaguchi, K. and Ishino, H. and Koshio, Y. and Tada, T. and Ishizuka, T. and Barr, G. and Barrow, D. and Cook, L. and Samani, S. and Wark, D. and Holin, A. and Nova, F. and Jung, S. and Yoo, J. and Fannon, J. E. P. and Kneale, L. and Malek, M. and McElwee, J. M. and Peacock, T. and Stowell, P. and Thiesse, M. D. and Thompson, L. F. and Okazawa, H. and Lakshmi, S. M. and Kwon, E. and Lee, M. W. and Seo, J. W. and Yu, I. and Ashida, Y. and Ichikawa, A. K. and Nakamura, K. D. and Goto, S. and Hayasaki, H. and Kodama, S. and Kong, Y. and Masaki, Y. and Mizuno, Y. and Muro, T. and Nakagiri, K. and Nakajima, Y. and Taniuchi, N. and Yokoyama, M. and de Perio, P. and Fujita, S. and Jesús-Valls, C. and Martens, K. and Marti, Ll. and Tsui, K. M. and Vagins, M. R. and Xia, J. and Kuze, M. and Izumiyama, S. and Matsumoto, R. and Asaka, R. and Ishitsuka, M. and Sugo, M. and Wako, M. and Yamauchi, K. and Nakano, Y. and Cormier, F. and Gaur, R. and Hartz, M. and Konaka, A. and Li, X. and Smithers, B. R. and Chen, S. and Wu, Y. and Xu, B. D. and Zhang, A. Q. and Zhang, B. and Adhikary, H. and Girgus, M. and Govindaraj, P. and Posiadala-Zezula, M. and Prabhu, Y. S. and Boyd, S. B. and Edwards, R. and Hadley, D. and Nicholson, M. and O'Flaherty, M. and Richards, B. and Ali, A. and Jamieson, B. and Bronner, C. and Horiguchi, D. and Minamino, A. and Sasaki, Y. and Shibayama, R. and Shimamura, R.},
  title         = {First Associated Neutrino Search for a Failed Supernova Candidate with Super-Kamiokande},
  year          = {2025},
  month         = nov,
  abstract      = {In 2024, a failed supernova candidate, M31-2014-DS1, was reported in the Andromeda galaxy (M31), located at a distance of approximately 770 kpc. In this paper, we search for neutrinos from this failed supernova using data from Super-Kamiokande (SK). Based on the estimated time of black hole formation inferred from optical and infrared observations, we define a search window for neutrino events in the SK data. Using this window, we develop a dedicated analysis method for failed supernovae and apply it to M31-2014-DS1, by conducting a cluster search using the timing and energy information of candidate events. No significant neutrino excess is observed within the search region. Consequently, we place an upper limit on the electron antineutrino luminosity from M31-2014-DS1 and discuss its implications for various failed SN models and their neutrino emission characteristics. Despite the 18 MeV threshold adopted to suppress backgrounds, the search remains sufficiently sensitive to constrain the Shen-TM1 EOS, yielding a 90% confidence level upper limit of 1.76 \times 10^{53} erg on the electron antineutrino luminosity, slightly above the expected value of 1.35 \times 10^{53} erg.},
  archiveprefix = {arXiv},
  copyright     = {arXiv.org perpetual, non-exclusive license},
  doi           = {10.48550/ARXIV.2511.03470},
  eprint        = {2511.03470},
